# Render Logs Access

When debugging production issues, you can query Render logs directly instead of asking the user to check them.

## Endpoint

```
GET https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs
Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb
```

## Query Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `minutes` | number | 30 | Fetch logs from last N minutes |
| `startTime` | ISO string | - | Specific start time (UTC) |
| `endTime` | ISO string | - | Specific end time (UTC) |
| `limit` | number | 200 | Max number of log entries |
| `search` | string | - | Filter logs containing this text (case-insensitive) |

## Example Queries

**IMPORTANT**: On Windows, use `curl.exe` (not PowerShell's `Invoke-WebRequest` which times out).

```bash
# Recent logs (last 5 minutes)
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?minutes=5&limit=50"

# Search for errors
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?minutes=30&search=ERROR"

# Specific time window (UTC)
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?startTime=2026-02-10T10:24:00Z&endTime=2026-02-10T10:25:00Z"

# Inbound email logs
curl.exe -s -H "Authorization: Bearer Diamond9753!!@@pb" "https://pb-webhook-server.onrender.com/debug-render-logs?search=INBOUND-EMAIL&minutes=60"
```

## When to Use

- User reports something isn't working
- Need to investigate webhook failures
- Checking if a feature is being triggered
- Debugging errors in production

**Do not ask the user to check Render logs manually** - query them yourself using this endpoint.
